entry.title: Fix tough scrollbar scrolling cases for linux.
entry.content:
The original logic for capturing the thumb in these tests was

calculating the width of the viewport incorrectly and causing the

scrollbar to not be grabbed. The issue is explained in more detail in

the linked bug. Both fluent scrollbars and Linux default scrollbars are

15 pixels wide, making the original calculations wrong for them.



This CL makes Linux use the logic that correctly calculates where the

thumb will be and drag it correctly.



I had originally separated the two code paths between windows and other

platforms because my original fix had introduced some perf regressions

that I hadn't confirmed the root cause of. Now we know (explained and

shown in the linked bug) that the original fix was indeed correct and

the separation of logic is not necessary. The performance metrics are

being impacted because the tests are now working properly.

Previously, the AX tree dump would only output the names of any ATK

relations on a node. This means we couldn't make assertions on the

targets a relation needs to point to - for example, we might want to

assert that a relation points to a specific number of targets.



Now, we will output the roles of any nodes that an ATK relation

points to. We will also update existing tests accordingly.

entry.title: Multiple improvements to CronetTestRule and tests in general.
entry.content:
- It's now easier and less boilerplaty to get an appropriate CronetEngine

for a particular test case

- It's easier to clean up resources after a single test case

- It's easier to obtain a Cronet builder of the right type

- It's easier to write tests for additional Cronet implementations,

namely the AOSP-backed one



Prevoiusly, the test rule only returned a flag about which

implementation was being tested without any additional support.

This setup relies on tests proactively checking which implementation is

being tested and altering their behavior based on that. Many tests didn't,

and gave false information about correctness of (mainly) the Java only

implementation.



The new setup isn't perfect either and is prone to reusing resources of

the CronetTestRule if one isn't careful, especially with parallelized test

runners. At least it's better than what we had before, hopefully.

entry.title: Do not DCHECK when a deprecated extension disable reason is observed
entry.content:
Every now and then some Chrome clients report extensions with deprecated

disable reasons (eg. DISABLE_REMOTELY_FOR_MALWARE). This can happen when

the clients were not updated to execute migration code that removes

these reasons from the extension prefs. The GetDisableReasons function

in //c/b/m/extensions_metrics_provider.cc DCHECKs when this situation

occurs.

This CL removes the DCHECK. Instead, a histogram is emitted that records

the bitmask of such deprecated disable reason(s). The histogram provides

visibility into any potential problems with migration without causing

crashes.

entry.title: Implement "BeforeMatch" behavior in AnnotationAgent
entry.content:
A text fragment targeting text in a hidden but showable subtree will

cause the subtree to become visible. E.g. if the text is in a
,

has content-visibility: auto, or has the hidden=until-none attribute.



This behavior is currently implemented in TextFragmentAnchor. This CL

moves the behavior into AnnotationAgentImpl so it is more widely

available to other users of the Annotation API (e.g. user-notes, Chrome

Companion).



As part of this, we do a bit of cleanup and refactoring. The most

notable is that we no longer force an async break after text matching

unless the match is in a hidden subtree (so we can remove all the

double-rAFs from tests.



Motivation: this behavior is desired in Chrome Search Companion since

they use the kTextFinder annotations to perform a search of the document

to check if a text selector "works" in order to then offer up a text

directive link. This behavior is currently broken since the kTextFinder

"succeeds" as a match is found, however, the offered link does not work

since AnnotationAgent cannot open a hidden=until-none section.



This CL additionally makes kTextFinder side-effect free (doesn't

activate any locked DOM, doesn't create document markers) to make this

use case work.

Multiplanar SharedImages on Mac. A few notes:



* I tested the flow with Google Meet visual effects, which I confirmed

(repeatedly :) were broken if the flow wasn't correct

be required on other platforms

media/renderers/video_frame_rgba_to_yuva_converter.cc in response to

might need to be generalized in the future.

is invoked in this flow is WebGraphicsContext3DVideoFramePool, but I

filled in the others for completeness



This patch is based on a prototype by hitawala@.

entry.title: Generate stdlib GN rules from the Rust src tree when rolling Rust
entry.content:
This avoids the need to:

1. Build gnrt locally

2. Then download the roll CL

3. Copy Rust packages to prod

4. gclient sync

5. Run `gnrt gen --for-std`

6. Reupload the CL



In order to have the Rust roll pass the trybots.



upload_revision.py will, when rolling rust, do the `cargo vendor`

step in the Rust git checkout to get its dependencies, install

cargo and rustc in a sysroot, build `gnrt` using cargo, and then

run `gnrt gen --for-std=third_party/rust_src/src` which regenerates

the GN rules for the Rust stdlib from the updated version of Rust.



Previously gnrt gen --for-std would generate rules from the Rust

library found in //third_party/rust-toolchain, but that requires

Rust to already be rolled, so this now uses the feature of specifying

the Rust source tree root to --for-std.

entry.title: [//media] Copy only source size in CopyRGBATextureToVideoFrame()
entry.content:
In CopyRGBATextureToVideoFrame(), the codepath that goes through

CopySharedImage() currently specifies that the size of the rect to be

copied should be the coded size of the destination video frame. This is

incorrect: it should be the size of the source texture. This can

concretely lead to problems when the original size of the video needs

to be rounded up for alignment [1], as in this case the coded size of

the destination frame will be larger than the size of the source

texture and CopySharedImage() will raise an error.



When the destination SI is multiplanar (as it is in this case),

CopySharedImageHelper::CopySharedImage() clears the destination and

then copies exactly the specified rect. Hence this case is not

problematic from the service side.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:media/video/renderable_gpu_memory_buffer_video_frame_pool.cc;l=173-179

both legacy and non-legacy multi-planar shared images. Make the Graphite

wrap them in graphite backend textures.

3) for true single-plane images, wrap the dawn representation's texture

in a graphite backend texture like the current implementation.

with or without multiplane video flags.

entry.title: Implement double press and drag selection for web content.
entry.content:
Currently, users can double tap to select a word in an editable

environment. This CL allows users to expand the selection after a

double press by directly dragging after the second tap down (without

lifting after the tap down). This is similar to existing long press

drag behaviour, but initiated by a double press instead of a long press.



Summary of approach:



1. Add a tap_down_count property to kGestureTapDown events.

2. In blink::GestureManager, add selection behaviour to

HandleGestureTapDown if the tap down has tap_down_count > 1.

(Previously, the selection behaviour only occurred on the tap event.)

3. Re-use the existing LongPressDragSelector by allowing drag selection

to be initiated by a double press as well as a long press.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kZeGeGXkBlNsIRVLs27YWuOEVqfn4IH1U1sxmqZ5QYU/edit?usp=sharing&resourcekey=0-I-9oPhncwGvKJeSMRe7kTA

entry.title: [iOS][Bkmrks] Handle ancestor folder deletion in bookmarks code
entry.content:
Ancestor folder deletion was not properly handled in the following 3

bookmark classes.

- BookmarksEditorMediator: BookmarksEditorMediator needs to dismiss

view when any ancestor of the `self.bookmark` is deleted.

If however any ancestor of the `self.folder` is deleted then a

default parent folder is set to `mobile_node()` of the corresponding

bookmark model.

Also all instances of `_bookmark = nullptr` has been replaced with

`[self.delegate bookmarkEditorMediatorWantsDismissal:self]`. This

guarantees the invariant that `_bookmark` is never `nullptr`. Thus

avoiding the check `if (_bookmark) {...}` every time this variable is

accessed. Currently the code does not do this check which could

potentially create other bugs.

- BookmarksHomeMediator: If any ancestor of `self.displayedNode` is

deleted then `self.displayedNode` is set to `nullptr`.

- BookmarksFolderEditorViewController: If any ancestor of

`_folder` is deleted then this view is dismissed.

If however any ancestor of `_parentFolder` is deleted then a default

parent folder is set to `mobile_node()` of the corresponding

bookmark model.

Similar to `BookmarksEditorMediator` we ensure the invariant that

`_parentFolder` is never `nullptr`. Every `_parentFolder = nullptr` is

converted to `[self dismiss]`.

used to set a mock before it is yanked by

easily set and reset expectations. Tests have no care about when

fake enrollment launchers, connected to the mock, are created and used.

Tests can inject fake enrollment launchers via factory override.

entry.title: Prerender: Allow prerendering pages to create blob URL
entry.content:
Previously, prerendering pages cannot create blob URLs, as this API

uses a sync IPC to communicate, and we would cancel prerendering by

default in this case to ensure prerendering is safe.

After auditing it (see reasoning), we think creating an object URL seems

safe, and we can grant it during prerendering.



Reasoning:

- The blob url should be same-origin as the prerendering origin, so we

do not touch other origins.

- The security concerns should be addressed by this API.

https://w3c.github.io/FileAPI/#security-discussion

entry.title: [iOS] Fix Incognito intersitial with Locked Incognito tabs
entry.content:
This CL fixes an issue with the Incognito interstitial i.e. opening an

external link in Incognito through the interstitial fails if the user

has locked their Incognito tabs. This occurs because the reauth agent

dismisses all view controllers presented over the browser, including the

Incognito interstitial (this happens in the scene controller). As a

result, the Incognito interstitial coordinator is stopped and `self` is

nil in the reauth callback, so the tab opener cannot be invoked.



Possible solutions:

1. Make the interstitial an exception to that dismissal behavior.

2. Refactor the completion passed to the reauth agent so that `self` is

not required anymore.

3. Simplify the interstitial by abstracting away the reauth requirement

and instead simply forwarding the responsibility to invoke reauth to

the tab opener.

This CL implements the latter.



Fixed: 1450484

Following up on the new API ExtendSelectionAndReplace/ReplaceSurroundingText that was recently introduced into ChromeOS inputs, we want to have an option that moves the caret right after the committed text. This caret behavior is necessary for some ChromeOS features, including autocorrect.



This CL extends InputMethodController::ReplaceText to have another parameter that can allow us to move the caret right after the committed text.

entry.title: [lacros] Add additional logging for session debugging
entry.content:
This CL adds further logging to command_storage_backend and some

lacros-specific logging to callsites of LoadTabsFromLastSession().



For affected users, session reads are triggered for both tab

and session restore when the lacros process is first started in

windowless mode. This does not occur for unaffected users.

Understanding what specifically is tripping this code path should

help in root causing the restore failures.



Logs in the command_storage_backend will give better insight into

how session files are being handled. Logs in code calling

TabRestoreService::LoadTabsFromLastSession() will help to understand

if this is being run at unexpected times during startup, potentially

influencing the resulting restore state.



Lacros specific overrides to the VLOG level at these callsites

have been added to avoid users needing to run the latest version

of both ash and lacros for the logs to begin appearing in user logs.



Bug: 1424800, 1450427
